The paper deals with steganography in real-time services like Voice over IP, which falls under the category of network security (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the impact of steganography on the quality of voice transmission, which is related to signal processing (cs.SD) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents a new hidden data insertion procedure and compares it to a previous approach, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR, followed by cs.MM, cs.NI, cs.SD, and cs.IT.
